body_html:
@efeiefei : The device probably doesn't support NNAPI, also even if you use NNAPI it could be the case that NNAPI is using CPU fallback so there is no speed up.
Regarding results being wrong, we recently fixed a few bugs in NNAPI delegation, make sure you are using the latest build.

@efeiefei : The device probably doesn't support NNAPI, also even if you use NNAPI it could be the case that NNAPI is using CPU fallback so there is no speed up.
Regarding results being wrong, we recently fixed a few bugs in NNAPI delegation, make sure you are using the latest build.
